The paper focuses on comparing the output accuracy of discrete event simulation and agent-based simulation models in studying human-centric complex systems, specifically in the retail sector. This falls under the categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), systems and control (cs.SY), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
